The paper discusses the use of game theory in cybersecurity, specifically in the context of deception and counter-deception. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of game theory and mechanism design theory, which are both sub-fields of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the physical impact of attack and defense strategies, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The paper's focus on cyber deception and the use of game theory to address it suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of diverse methodologies from game theory suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
